  carbohydrates: 54 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 41 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 670 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/beef-tenderloin-topped-demi-glace-5d9e13a7168569635b1a884b
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
---

Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and halve
@Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Zest
and halve @Lemon{1}. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch
pieces (no need to peel); place in a large #pot{} with enough salted water to
cover. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup
potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} in same pot over low heat. Add minced garlic and
cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Return potatoes to pot; mash with a
#potato masher{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking
liquid as needed. Stir in @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}; season with @Salt{} and
@Pepper{}. Keep covered until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, toss Brussels sprouts in a large #bowl{} with a large drizzle of
@Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Place Brussels sprouts
and 1 lemon half cut side down on a #baking sheet{}. Roast on top rack
until golden brown, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{};
season generously with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of
@Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef and
cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a
#cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add remaining
@Garlic{1%clove} and @Rosemary{1%sprig}; cook, stirring, until fragrant,
~{30-60%seconds}. Reduce heat to low. Add @Beef Demi-Glace{1} and
@Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon} and @Water{¼%cup}. Cook, stirring, until thoroughly
combined, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in any resting juices from beef. Turn off heat.
Season with salt and pepper. Remove and discard garlic and rosemary.

Slice beef against the grain. Top Brussels sprouts with as much juice from
roasted lemon as you like; sprinkle with lemon zest and @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon}
to taste. Divide beef, Brussels sprouts, and mashed potatoes between plates.
Spoon sauce over beef and serve.

> You haven't tasted steak quite like this before: this melt-in-your-mouth beef
> tenderloin is spooned with a rich, rosemary-flecked pan sauce to bring its
> meatiness to the maximum. On the side, creamy garlic mashed potatoes and
> crispy roasted lemon Brussels sprouts so good, you may not want to share.